    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# 💾 CV Slack Bot – Save to Sheet & Card Actions\n\nHandles button clicks from the Block Kit cards posted by **Workflow A**. When a recruiter clicks **💾 Save to Sheet**, the candidate is flattened into a row and appended to a Google Sheet, then the card updates to confirm. **Dismiss** simply removes the card.\n\nThis is the \"do something\" half of the recruiter Slack bot – Workflow A is read-only. Both are needed for the full lookup-and-save loop.\n\n## ⚙️ How It Works\n1. **Receive Button Click** – webhook listens for Slack interactivity POSTs\n2. **Acknowledge Slack** – fires in parallel to beat Slack's 3-second timeout\n3. **Parse Slack Action Payload** – unpacks the form-encoded payload, extracts the candidate JSON\n4. **Route by Action** – routes by `action_id` (save_to_sheet vs dismiss)\n5. **Flatten Candidate Data** – splits nested JSON into 30 discrete Sheet columns\n6. **Append to Candidates Sheet** – adds the row to the Sheet\n7. **Update Card: Saved** – edits the Slack card to \"✅ Saved by @user\"\n8. **Delete Card on Dismiss** – removes the card on Dismiss clicks\n\n## 🛠️ Setup Guide\n### 1. Prepare the Google Sheet\n- Create a new Google Sheet\n- Add a tab named exactly `Candidates`\n- Paste this header row into A1 (Sheets will auto-split on commas if you say yes):",
        "height": 816,
        "width": 480
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "position": [
        -1344,
        -224
      ],
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "id": "a7d38384-e9ff-4503-8802-55785ffe863f",
      "name": "Sticky Note5"
    }
